review_title: Nice fit , needs a few improvements
reviews: I got the 14 to 16 inch one for my 2006 Rockwood premiere , fit is great, not sure on the durability as I just got it , one thing I would suggest the manufacturer do is add clips or sew the top flap to the strap pull downs , the wind just blows the top flap up and exposes the mesh air holes which will let water and snow get in and trapped on trailer . My wife will sew them to the straps .

I'm 6'6" inch tall 230 pounds, the XL fits good not too baggy also not too tight , wore it fishing in the sun , felt great and kept me cool, nice breathable mesh going up the sides under arms and on arms

Bend the tab use a existing screw hole and cut the connectors that came with it off then just connect the yellow to yellow black to black and red to red ( didn't use the white ) from the old OEM camera wire harness . I put black silicone around it to fill in the gaps and make it all water tight .

review_title: Nice , lacks a plug to protect the charge port
reviews: Nice case for the price , pairs well with a tempered glass screen protector, kick stand works , one downside is there is no rubber plug to protect the charge port

review_title: Stays hot for a couple hours max
reviews: Used this at a event where I was selling coffee , I put boiling water in these and closed lid and let stand for 15 min then filled with fresh hot coffee , the coffee stayed hot for a maximum of 1.5 to 2 hours , seller was good and replaced mine so I changed to 4 stars
Charged it over night then used it , and if lasted 30 min then died , tried to charge it and the charge wire melted , cheap crap

review_title: Great if you want to excersise your arms
reviews: Ok so ya it works but the amount of time and turns it takes to grind a medium to fine grind is crazy , like I have to sit down and turn this thing for like 10 min , it's better if you save your money and buy a handgrinder that has bigger burrs
Nice cover , a bit baggy for my 17 foot bayliner , i ended up building a cover support and also pulled it over the outboard just to snug it up

Nice little kettle , pours nice, takes 5:25 minutes to reach boil ( kind of long ) , also the cord is super short , for this price point you cant gi wrong , if you have a little more money go for the bonavita .

review_title: This is the best phone on the market and also the most fragile
reviews: This is the best phone on the market and also the most fragile , even with a otterbox case my screen shattered with just a one foot drop to my counter

I dropped phone from 1 foot from my hand to kitchen sink and the screen cracked ! This case provides no protection whatsoever along the side edges of your screen , only on the top and bottom of phone . So if you buy this pray that when it falls it falls perfectly
